      • setAutoGeneralize

        public final void setAutoGeneralize(boolean autoGeneralize)
        Set the autoGeneralize parameter.
        Parameters:
        autoGeneralize - - Enable or disable the auto generalization of features from a non-editable layer in on-demand mode. When true, the layer uses the current map resolution as the maxAllowableOffset for all queries issued to the server. The default value is true. As of v2.7

      • setDisplayOnPan

        public final void setDisplayOnPan(boolean displayOnPan)
        Set default behavior for graphics.
        Parameters:
        displayOnPan - - When true, graphics are displayed during panning. When false, the graphics are turned off during pan movement. Setting to false may improve performance in Internet Explorer. The default is true.

      • setTileHeight

        public final void setTileHeight(int tileHeight)
        Set the tileHeight parameter.
        Parameters:
        tileHeight - - Specify the size of the virtual tiles, used in on-demand mode. The virtual tile scheme is used in on-demand mode to make effective use of browser caching. The default value is 512. This option is only valid in on-demand mode and must be a square. For example, specifying a value like 512x256 is not supported.

      • setTileWidth

        tileWidth - - Specify the size of the virtual tiles, used in on-demand mode. The virtual tile scheme is used in on-demand mode to make effective use of browser caching. The default value is 512. This option is only valid in on-demand mode and must be a square. For example, specifying a value like 512x256 is not supported.
